<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF7B6AC4F826924C16B7BE10" pageId="128" pageNumber="887" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7B6AC4F826924C16B7BE10" blockId="128.[2009,2603,887,1314]" pageId="128" pageNumber="887">
Based on multivariate analyses of forearm and cranial measurements, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7B6AC4F6989218140FBF6C" authority="(Cretzschmar, 1826)" authorityName="Cretzschmar" box="[2404,2575,1089,1118]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="887" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">S. leucogaster</taxonomicName>
is distinct from S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7B6AC4F73F923D1713BFB7" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[2243,2323,1124,1157]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="887" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">viridis</taxonomicName>
but includes damarensis, which might occupy a different ecological niche compared with northern populations of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7B6AC4F74692831768BFC9" authority="(Cretzschmar, 1826)" authorityName="Cretzschmar" box="[2234,2408,1242,1275]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="887" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">S. leucogaster</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
